<h1>Input</h1>
<br><br>
<p>Wraps the <a href="https://github.com/DockYard/ember-one-way-controls/blob/master/docs/one-way-input.md">ember-one-way-input</a></p>
<p>
  <table>
    <tr>
      <th>Paramater</th>
      <th>Type</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>
    <tr><td>value</td><td>string</td><td>The value of the input (even 'number' type returns a string)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>label</td><td>string</td><td>Label</td></tr>
    <tr><td>type</td> <td>string ('text' default)</td><td>The type of the input (html5 values apply)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>required</td> <td>true, false(default)</td><td>Indicates whether this is a required field - adds an '*' to the UI and marks the input element as 'required'</td></tr>
    <tr><td>disabled</td> <td>true, false(default)</td><td>Indicates whether the field is disabled</td></tr>
    <tr><td>placeholder</td> <td>string</td><td>Element placeholder text</td></tr>
    <tr><td>class</td> <td>string</td><td>Element css classes</td></tr>
    <tr><td>elementId</td> <td>string</td><td>Textarea will be 'input-[id]'</td></tr>
    <tr><td>errors</td> <td>[object]</td><td>Array of error objects.  Each object must contain a 'message' key to be displayed</td></tr>
    <tr><td>update</td> <td>function (value(string)</td><td>The function that returns the current value each time it changes</td></tr>
  </table>
</p>

<h3>Valid sdsf</h3>
{{mediasuite-input
  value=model.firstName
  type='text'
  label="First Name:"
  required=true
  disabled=false
  placeholder='Example Name'
  class='skinned-text-area'
  elementId='first-name'
  update=(action (mut form.firstName))
}}
